{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <p>A call to action is used to entice users to select a link or display hidden content, depending on the style. For example, use the Primary style to bring attention to an important link or use the Brick style to organize links in a grid that can also display hidden content.</p>

  <h3>Navigation vs. action</h3>

  <p>Use calls to action only as navigational elements and use <a href="../button">Buttons</a> to perform actions. Calls to action and buttons have stylistic differences, even though they look similar.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Calls to action are used more in layouts whereas buttons are used more in components.</li>
    <li>The text labels in calls to action are larger and thicker than the text labels in buttons.</li>
    <li>A call to action background container has more padding than a button background container.</li>
    <li>A Primary call to action has a red background whereas a Primary button has a blue background.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Text labels</h3>

  <p>Call to action text labels are written differently than button text labels. Call to action text labels should be more creative or expressive to better entice users to make a selection.</p>

